{
  "slug": "roast-pork-loin-with-crackling",
  "tutorialId": "cmp73vfr80001wkv4gl1mryli",
  "capturedAt": "2026-05-30T18:25:00.397Z",
  "preFix": {
    "title": "Roast pork loin with crackling",
    "subtitle": "Scored skin, overnight dry, hot oven start",
    "excerpt": "Pork loin roasted with its skin on, the rind scored and dried overnight so it blisters into crisp crackling. Served with apple sauce.",
    "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136. Roast pork entries and crackling method.\n\nEliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845), Project Gutenberg. Roast pork with crisp rind.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pork loin with crackling delivers two textures in one joint: tender, juicy meat inside and a crisp, salty rind on top. The crackling is the prize. Getting it right requires scored rind, a completely dry surface, and a very hot oven blast at the start.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The overnight dry-salt stage is the most important step. Salt draws moisture from the rind; a dry rind crisps rather than steams.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "ingredientsList",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "name": "Pork loin",
                "unit": "g",
                "amount": 1800,
                "prepNote": "bone-in or boneless, rind on",
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f4af002drkv42usg3xcq",
                "ingredientSlug": "pork-loin"
              },
              {
                "name": "Sea salt flakes",
                "unit": "tsp",
                "amount": 3,
                "prepNote": "for the rind",
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f7ll0087rkv43k6j3dft",
                "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-flakes"
              },
              {
                "name": "Fine sea salt",
                "unit": "tsp",
                "amount": 1,
                "prepNote": "for the flesh side",
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
                "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
              },
              {
                "name": "Ground black pepper",
                "unit": "tsp",
                "amount": 1,
                "prepNote": null,
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp871q6g00092wv4g1jc4y3b",
                "ingredientSlug": "black-pepper-ground"
              },
              {
                "name": "Fennel seeds",
                "unit": "tsp",
                "amount": 1,
                "prepNote": null,
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": true,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f81h008zrkv480za7gfd",
                "ingredientSlug": "fennel-seeds"
              },
              {
                "name": "Onion",
                "unit": "each",
                "amount": 2,
                "prepNote": "roughly sliced",
                "groupLabel": "For the trivet",
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f59k0042rkv4afimm5ox",
                "ingredientSlug": "onion"
              },
              {
                "name": "Bramley apple",
                "unit": "each",
                "amount": 2,
                "prepNote": "roughly chopped",
                "groupLabel": "For the trivet",
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f6mv006frkv49yoj5vsy",
                "ingredientSlug": "apple-bramley"
              }
            ],
            "defaultServings": 6
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "A sharp knife or a craft knife makes the cleanest score lines in the rind. Aim for lines 1 cm apart, cutting through the rind but not deep into the fat.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The night before",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Score the rind in parallel lines about 1 cm apart, cutting through the skin and just into the fat beneath.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Pat the rind completely dry. Rub the sea salt flakes firmly into the score marks. Leave uncovered in the fridge overnight.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Prepare for the oven",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Take the pork from the fridge an hour before cooking. Pat the rind dry again with kitchen paper if any moisture has beaded on the surface.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Rub the flesh side and edges with the fine salt, pepper, and fennel seeds if using. Heat the oven to 230 degrees C fan.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Scatter the onion and Bramley apple across the base of the roasting pan and set the rack on top. Place the pork rind-side up on the rack.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Roast at 230 degrees C for 30 minutes to blister the rind into ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "crackling",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpdr2rmg0000vkv4eurv2hwe"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ". Watch carefully; if it is catching and darkening too fast, reduce the heat slightly.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Reduce to 180 degrees C and continue roasting until the probe reads 68 degrees C at the thickest point of the meat, away from any bone. This takes about 60 to 70 more minutes for a 1.8 kg joint.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Rest and carve",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Transfer to a warm board and ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "rest",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmp73twkn0001p8v4kyryolap"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " for 20 minutes. Do not cover the rind with foil or it will soften.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Cut down through the crackling between the score lines. Carve the meat into slices and serve with a piece of crackling on each plate.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Overnight drying is essential. If the crackling is still soft after 30 minutes at 230 degrees C, turn the grill on for 5 minutes, watching closely.",
                "cause": "The rind was not dry enough, or the oven was not hot enough at the start.",
                "symptom": "The crackling is soft rather than crisp"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Score firmly through the rind and top layer of fat. The initial blast needs to be a full 230 degrees C.",
                "cause": "The score lines were too shallow, or the heat was not high enough to make the rind blister.",
                "symptom": "The crackling is hard and tough rather than crunchy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Pull at 68 to 70 degrees C and rest well. Loin dries out quickly if overcooked.",
                "cause": "Overcooked above 72 degrees C.",
                "symptom": "The meat is dry"
              },
              {
                "fix": "If the joint is uneven, prop the lower end with a wedge of onion so the rind sits level across the whole surface.",
                "cause": "The joint was not sitting level in the tin.",
                "symptom": "Rind is uneven: some crisp, some soft"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pork belly gives even more generous crackling and a richer result. Score and dry the same way, but roast for three hours at 160 degrees C after the initial blast rather than probing for a set internal temperature.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Crackling has been the mark of a well-roasted pig in British cooking since at least the eighteenth century. Charles Lamb, in his Dissertation on Roast Pig, describes the discovery of crackling with mock-heroic reverence. Modern butchers score it as a matter of course; the cook just has to dry it properly.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 6,
    "yieldDescription": null,
    "difficulty": "INTERMEDIATE"
  },
